message: Anyone watching the new Hawaii Five-O? I'm wondering if it's worth giving it a chance.
yep it is, I enjoy it. So probably will be cancelled soon, just my luck

What happened to it this week ?

I listed Hawaii Five-O as one of my guilty pleasures. I especially enjoy Scott Caan. Seeing "Jin" from Lost and Grace Park from Battlestar G. is fun, too. In addition, being up here in coooooold Minnesota, seeing the super-saturated colors of Hawaii on the show simply does my eyes some good.
i didnt like it at all
@adamsstephen I am always apprehensive these days that I will get into a show and then they pull the plug on it after 1 season. I hate it when that happens!

I first watched (after the Super Bowl perhaps) out of nostalgia as I used to sneak to watch it when I was a kid. But, I got hooked, really hooked. It is my guilty pleasure and rather well done for the genre.
I really enjoy watching it, cbs says the ratings are pretty high. so they'll probalby do another season.
